President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring May 14, 2017, as Mother's Day in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the special celebration of mothers and the importance of motherhood to the prosperity of families, communities, and the nation. It recognizes the strength, spirit, and selflessness of mothers, who shape the character of each new generation and teach the power and joy of unconditional love. The proclamation also acknowledges the contributions of mothers to American families and the nation, as designated by a joint resolution approved by Congress in 1914.